reviewText: I bought this DVD for my 3 year old son for Halloween this year and he has watched it everyday since.  He loves it! reviewText: HOWL-ling fun for Nicktoon fans.FROM THE BACK COVER:Bubble, BubbleThere's toil and trouble this Halloween when this cast of characters takes to the streets for candy and treats. And they wind up with so much more that they never expected! Boo!SpongeBob SquarePants-"Scaredy Pants"It's Halloween and SpongeBob has the scariest costume ever-the Flying Dutchman, Bikini Bottom's ghostly legend.Rugrats-"Curse of the Werewuff"Angelica's up to no good when she tricks the babies into believing that whatever they're dressed as for Halloween, they'll turn into the day after. Unless, of course, they give her all of their candy!Nickelodeon Rocket Power- "It Came From Planet Merve"After Twister reads a book about an alien invasion, he starts seeing eerie similarities between the characters in the book and Merv Stimpleton!"Netherworld Night"The Rocket gang is invited to a sleepover campout at Eddie's house. And Lars sees it as the perfect opportunity to enlist his crew and pull off the scariest prank ever!Hey Arnold! "Arnold's Halloween"When Grandpa won't let Arnold help plan the annual fright-fest, Arnold becomes determined to out-scare Grandpa.The Fairy OddParents-"Scary Godparents"Halloween is turning into a real bummer for Tommy, who's trick-or-treating as a mummy wrapped in toilet paper. So he asks Cosmo and Wanda to make him "real and scary".It's a great spook-taculer fun DVD for the Nicktoon fans.

reviewText: I love this DVD as I am quite the connoisseur of Halloween specials; I can't get enough of them! Hey Arnold's 'Arnold's Halloween' strikes the jackpot with its War of the Worlds inspired storyline; it's sufficiantly moody and fun. Rugrats' 'Curse of the Werewuff' is a new entry into Nick's Halloween canon and a welcome one at that. A show that has become too precious as of late, this stops before going to far with its own "cuteness". I still prefer thir original Halloween episode 'Candy Bar Creep Show', but 'Werewuff' is still highly enjoyable! The Fairly Odd Parent's 'Scary GodParents' is equally hip and funny and SpongeBob SquarePants' 'Scaredy Pants' is perfect. Only the strange inclusion of two non-Halloween related Rocket Power stories stops me forom giving this a five-star rating; they have a Halloween epsiode so why wasn't it included? Their two entires seem pointless and only one is anywhere near being holiday themed. With so many great Halloween epsiodes left off the DVD, one has to wonder at this choice.
Title: Nicktoons - Halloween - Tales of Fright
